title: For Sale:  Saiga 12 SBS Shotgun
postcontent:
WTS Russian Saiga 12 SBS w/ 11.5" barrel w/ accessories, magazines

These have been banned from import via sanctions against Russia and are becoming hard to find. I am somewhat recoil sensative after a neck injury

The pistol grip conversion was professionally done: extra reciever holes welded over and blended, original trigger guard reloacted and welded, back plate welded onto the receiver, carrier group polished and reshaped to ease inserting magazine on a closed bolt action work/polish, Tapco G2 trigger group and SAW grip, customized selector lever for use w/ left thumb, and duracoated Foliage green. 

The barrel was shortened (and re-threaded) later on a Form 1 per the National Firearms Act. I rented a guided thread die for the new muzzle threads, it indexed in the bore to ensure the threads are straight & concentric. 

Side folding AR M4 type stock w/ butt modification to allow it to fully fold w/ 20 drum inserted.

SGM tri rail hanguard, VFG, VT Flashlight mount and Surefire G2L light, SAW grip, 4 position gas regulator, Tromix Shark breacher brake, Tromix Bolt on knurled charging handle knob, couple reduced power action spring for shooting light loads. 

Gun and magazines are lightly used, just a few range trips to function test really.

One 5rd factory magazine comes w/ the gun, I have a couple 12 rd drums and 10 rd stick mags that I'll sell too w/ the gun, I sold the 20.

All NFA rules apply. (per the NFA [National Firearms Act] if you want to buy this gun as a SBS, you will have to send a "Form 4" along w/ $200 to the Federal Government & pass a background check. When they send the form back approved several months later, you could then take possession of the gun.) 

Or, you can put down $150, I can have the barrel pulled, then I can sell you the rest of the parts as a normal title 1 shotgun/receiver and you can submit your own form 1 (or eForm1). When you get the form one back approved you can then take possession of the barrel and take it to the smith for reinstallation.  The $150 will cover the smith to take it out & put it back in.  

Prefer to transfer direct to another FL resident who is a CCW &/or NFA Tax stamp holder, or directly to a Title II/Class 3 dealer.  Non FL residents will have to go through a dealer if it goes as an NFA item on a Form 4
